{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":354,"text":"Chris Anderson: Elon, what kind of crazy dream"},{"time":3486,"text":"would persuade you to think of trying"},{"time":5642,"text":"to take on the auto industry and build an all-electric car?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9000,"text":"Elon Musk: Well, it goes back to when I was in university."},{"time":12402,"text":"I thought about, what are the problems that are most likely"},{"time":14554,"text":"to affect the future of the world or the future of humanity?"},{"time":17626,"text":"I think it's extremely important that we have sustainable transport"},{"time":21118,"text":"and sustainable energy production."},{"time":23477,"text":"That sort of overall sustainable energy problem"},{"time":25522,"text":"is the biggest problem that we have to solve this century,"},{"time":28021,"text":"independent of environmental concerns."},{"time":30226,"text":"In fact, even if producing CO2 was good for the environment,"},{"time":33143,"text":"given that we're going to run out of hydrocarbons,"},{"time":36223,"text":"we need to find some sustainable means of operating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40278,"text":"CA: Most of American electricity comes from"},{"time":44288,"text":"burning fossil fuels."},{"time":45950,"text":"How can an electric car that plugs into that electricity help?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":50565,"text":"EM: Right. There's two elements to that answer."},{"time":53524,"text":"One is that, even if you take the same source fuel"},{"time":56484,"text":"and produce power at the power plant"},{"time":58473,"text":"and use it to charge electric cars, you're still better off."},{"time":61367,"text":"So if you take, say, natural gas,"},{"time":63346,"text":"which is the most prevalent hydrocarbon source fuel,"},{"time":65954,"text":"if you burn that in a modern"},{"time":68952,"text":"General Electric natural gas turbine,"},{"time":71147,"text":"you'll get about 60 percent efficiency."},{"time":72985,"text":"If you put that same fuel in an internal combustion engine car,"},{"time":75696,"text":"you get about 20 percent efficiency."},{"time":77596,"text":"And the reason is, in the stationary power plant,"},{"time":79176,"text":"you can afford to have something that weighs a lot more,"},{"time":81544,"text":"is voluminous,"},{"time":83259,"text":"and you can take the waste heat"},{"time":84713,"text":"and run a steam turbine and generate"},{"time":86082,"text":"a secondary power source."},{"time":87866,"text":"So in effect, even after you've taken transmission loss into account and everything,"},{"time":91652,"text":"even using the same source fuel, you're at least twice as better off"},{"time":95056,"text":"charging an electric car, then burning it at the power plant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97528,"text":"CA: That scale delivers efficiency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99639,"text":"EM: Yes, it does."},{"time":101378,"text":"And then the other point is, we have to have sustainable means"},{"time":104396,"text":"of power generation anyway, electricity generation."},{"time":106799,"text":"So given that we have to solve sustainable electricity generation,"},{"time":109868,"text":"then it makes sense for us to have electric cars"},{"time":113333,"text":"as the mode of transport."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115908,"text":"CA: So we've got some video here"},{"time":117343,"text":"of the Tesla being assembled,"},{"time":119834,"text":"which, if we could play that first video --"},{"time":122548,"text":"So what is innovative about this process in this vehicle?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":127492,"text":"EM: Sure. So, in order to accelerate the advent of electric transport,"},{"time":131068,"text":"and I should say that I think, actually,"},{"time":133138,"text":"all modes of transport will become fully electric"},{"time":135596,"text":"with the ironic exception of rockets."},{"time":140663,"text":"There's just no way around Newton's third law."},{"time":143420,"text":"The question is how do you accelerate"},{"time":146872,"text":"the advent of electric transport?"},{"time":148452,"text":"And in order to do that for cars, you have to come up with"},{"time":150900,"text":"a really energy efficient car,"},{"time":153227,"text":"so that means making it incredibly light,"},{"time":155084,"text":"and so what you're seeing here"},{"time":156110,"text":"is the only all-aluminum body and chassis car"},{"time":158856,"text":"made in North America."},{"time":160442,"text":"In fact, we applied a lot of rocket design techniques"},{"time":163130,"text":"to make the car light despite having a very large battery pack."},{"time":166747,"text":"And then it also has the lowest drag coefficient"},{"time":168907,"text":"of any car of its size."},{"time":170275,"text":"So as a result, the energy usage is very low,"},{"time":173940,"text":"and it has the most advanced battery pack,"},{"time":176156,"text":"and that's what gives it the range that's competitive,"},{"time":178740,"text":"so you can actually have on the order of a 250-mile range."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181679,"text":"CA: I mean, those battery packs are incredibly heavy,"},{"time":185268,"text":"but you think the math can still work out intelligently --"},{"time":188539,"text":"by combining light body, heavy battery,"},{"time":190675,"text":"you can still gain spectacular efficiency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192948,"text":"EM: Exactly. The rest of the car has to be very light"},{"time":194780,"text":"to offset the mass of the pack,"},{"time":196541,"text":"and then you have to have a low drag coefficient so that you have good highway range."},{"time":199570,"text":"And in fact, customers of the Model S"},{"time":203295,"text":"are sort of competing with each other"},{"time":204374,"text":"to try to get the highest possible range."},{"time":207393,"text":"I think somebody recently got 420 miles out of a single charge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210923,"text":"CA: Bruno Bowden, who's here, did that,"},{"time":214011,"text":"broke the world record.EM: Congratulations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216601,"text":"CA: That was the good news. The bad news was that"},{"time":218213,"text":"to do it, he had to drive at 18 miles an hour constant speed"},{"time":221027,"text":"and got pulled over by the cops. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224939,"text":"EM: I mean, you can certainly drive --"},{"time":228829,"text":"if you drive it 65 miles an hour,"},{"time":231467,"text":"under normal conditions,"},{"time":233431,"text":"250 miles is a reasonable number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235315,"text":"CA: Let's show that second video"},{"time":236453,"text":"showing the Tesla in action on ice."},{"time":239299,"text":"Not at all a dig at The New York Times, this, by the way."},{"time":241967,"text":"What is the most surprising thing about the experience"},{"time":244382,"text":"of driving the car?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":245890,"text":"EM: In creating an electric car,"},{"time":247368,"text":"the responsiveness of the car is really incredible."},{"time":249766,"text":"So we wanted really to have people feel as though"},{"time":252453,"text":"they've almost got to mind meld with the car,"},{"time":254556,"text":"so you just feel like you and the car are kind of one,"},{"time":257730,"text":"and as you corner and accelerate, it just happens,"},{"time":261776,"text":"like the car has ESP."},{"time":263610,"text":"You can do that with an electric car because of its responsiveness."},{"time":266106,"text":"You can't do that with a gasoline car."},{"time":268233,"text":"I think that's really a profound difference,"},{"time":270215,"text":"and people only experience that when they have a test drive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273002,"text":"CA: I mean, this is a beautiful but expensive car."},{"time":277296,"text":"Is there a road map where this becomes"},{"time":280871,"text":"a mass-market vehicle?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282450,"text":"EM: Yeah. The goal of Tesla has always been"},{"time":285010,"text":"to have a sort of three-step process,"},{"time":287282,"text":"where version one was an expensive car at low volume,"},{"time":291048,"text":"version two is medium priced and medium volume,"},{"time":294113,"text":"and then version three would be low price, high volume."},{"time":296402,"text":"So we're at step two at this point."},{"time":298085,"text":"So we had a $100,000 sports car, which was the Roadster."},{"time":301035,"text":"Then we've got the Model S, which starts at around 50,000 dollars."},{"time":304034,"text":"And our third generation car, which should hopefully"},{"time":306138,"text":"be out in about three or four years"},{"time":307867,"text":"will be a $30,000 car."},{"time":310522,"text":"But whenever you've got really new technology,"},{"time":313004,"text":"it generally takes about three major versions"},{"time":315098,"text":"in order to make it a compelling mass-market product."},{"time":318318,"text":"And so I think we're making progress in that direction,"},{"time":321042,"text":"and I feel confident that we'll get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323314,"text":"CA: I mean, right now, if you've got a short commute,"},{"time":325223,"text":"you can drive, you can get back, you can charge it at home."},{"time":328971,"text":"There isn't a huge nationwide network of charging stations now that are fast."},{"time":333218,"text":"Do you see that coming, really, truly,"},{"time":336058,"text":"or just on a few key routes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338311,"text":"EM: There actually are far more charging stations"},{"time":341186,"text":"than people realize,"},{"time":343411,"text":"and at Tesla we developed something"},{"time":345770,"text":"called a Supercharging technology,"},{"time":347978,"text":"and we're offering that if you buy a Model S"},{"time":351290,"text":"for free, forever."},{"time":352755,"text":"And so this is something that maybe a lot of people don't realize."},{"time":355410,"text":"We actually have California and Nevada covered,"},{"time":358240,"text":"and we've got the Eastern seaboard"},{"time":360514,"text":"from Boston to D.C. covered."},{"time":362766,"text":"By the end of this year, you'll be able to drive"},{"time":364148,"text":"from L.A. to New York"},{"time":366291,"text":"just using the Supercharger network,"},{"time":367893,"text":"which charges at five times the rate of anything else."},{"time":372110,"text":"And the key thing is to have a ratio of drive to stop,"},{"time":376536,"text":"to stop time, of about six or seven."},{"time":379535,"text":"So if you drive for three hours,"},{"time":381765,"text":"you want to stop for 20 or 30 minutes,"},{"time":383403,"text":"because that's normally what people will stop for."},{"time":385900,"text":"So if you start a trip at 9 a.m.,"},{"time":388020,"text":"by noon you want to stop to have a bite to eat,"},{"time":390558,"text":"hit the restroom, coffee, and keep going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392297,"text":"CA: So your proposition to consumers is, for the full charge, it could take an hour."},{"time":395654,"text":"So it's common -- don't expect to be out of here in 10 minutes."},{"time":399630,"text":"Wait for an hour, but the good news is,"},{"time":401597,"text":"you're helping save the planet,"},{"time":403036,"text":"and by the way, the electricity is free. You don't pay anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405729,"text":"EM: Actually, what we're expecting is for people"},{"time":407593,"text":"to stop for about 20 to 30 minutes, not for an hour."},{"time":411118,"text":"It's actually better to drive for about maybe 160, 170 miles"},{"time":418846,"text":"and then stop for half an hour"},{"time":420944,"text":"and then keep going."},{"time":422309,"text":"That's the natural cadence of a trip."},{"time":425591,"text":"CA: All right. So this is only one string to your energy bow."},{"time":429972,"text":"You've been working on this solar company SolarCity."},{"time":432614,"text":"What's unusual about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":435126,"text":"EM: Well, as I mentioned earlier,"},{"time":437486,"text":"we have to have sustainable electricity production"},{"time":441126,"text":"as well as consumption,"},{"time":442774,"text":"so I'm quite confident that the primary means"},{"time":446596,"text":"of power generation will be solar."},{"time":449077,"text":"I mean, it's really indirect fusion, is what it is."},{"time":451412,"text":"We've got this giant fusion generator in the sky called the sun,"},{"time":454646,"text":"and we just need to tap a little bit of that energy"},{"time":457538,"text":"for purposes of human civilization."},{"time":460414,"text":"What most people know but don't realize they know"},{"time":462420,"text":"is that the world is almost entirely solar-powered already."},{"time":465774,"text":"If the sun wasn't there, we'd be a frozen ice ball"},{"time":469014,"text":"at three degrees Kelvin,"},{"time":471176,"text":"and the sun powers the entire system of precipitation."},{"time":474974,"text":"The whole ecosystem is solar-powered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477630,"text":"CA: But in a gallon of gasoline, you have,"},{"time":479981,"text":"effectively, thousands of years of sun power"},{"time":482245,"text":"compressed into a small space,"},{"time":484310,"text":"so it's hard to make the numbers work right now on solar,"},{"time":487289,"text":"and to remotely compete with, for example, natural gas,"},{"time":490378,"text":"fracked natural gas. How are you going to build a business here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493822,"text":"EM: Well actually, I'm confident that solar"},{"time":497131,"text":"will beat everything, hands down, including natural gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501047,"text":"(Applause)CA: How?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503434,"text":"EM: It must, actually. If it doesn't, we're in deep trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507007,"text":"CA: But you're not selling solar panels to consumers."},{"time":510041,"text":"What are you doing?"},{"time":511192,"text":"EM: No, we actually are. You can buy a solar system"},{"time":514440,"text":"or you can lease a solar system."},{"time":515982,"text":"Most people choose to lease."},{"time":517972,"text":"And the thing about solar power is that"},{"time":520038,"text":"it doesn't have any feed stock or operational costs,"},{"time":522789,"text":"so once it's installed, it's just there."},{"time":526014,"text":"It works for decades. It'll work for probably a century."},{"time":530515,"text":"So therefore, the key thing to do is to get the cost"},{"time":533453,"text":"of that initial installation low,"},{"time":535428,"text":"and then get the cost of the financing low,"},{"time":538063,"text":"because that interest -- those are the two factors that drive the cost of solar."},{"time":541687,"text":"And we've made huge progress in that direction,"},{"time":545103,"text":"and that's why I'm confident we'll actually beat natural gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548671,"text":"CA: So your current proposition to consumers is,"},{"time":551448,"text":"don't pay so much up front."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553664,"text":"EM: Zero.CA: Pay zero up front."},{"time":556344,"text":"We will install panels on your roof."},{"time":558983,"text":"You will then pay, how long is a typical lease?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562584,"text":"EM: Typical leases are 20 years,"},{"time":565828,"text":"but the value proposition is, as you're sort of alluding to, quite straightforward."},{"time":570491,"text":"It's no money down, and your utility bill decreases."},{"time":574641,"text":"Pretty good deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576521,"text":"CA: So that seems like a win for the consumer."},{"time":578434,"text":"No risk, you'll pay less than you're paying now."},{"time":580889,"text":"For you, the dream here then is that --"},{"time":583284,"text":"I mean, who owns the electricity from those panels for the longer term?"},{"time":588059,"text":"I mean, how do you, the company, benefit?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":591241,"text":"EM: Well, essentially,"},{"time":594783,"text":"SolarCity raises a chunk of capital"},{"time":600670,"text":"from say, a company or a bank."},{"time":604340,"text":"Google is one of our big partners here."},{"time":606553,"text":"And they have an expected return on that capital."},{"time":608977,"text":"With that capital, SolarCity purchases and installs the panel on the roof"},{"time":613363,"text":"and then charges the homeowner or business owner"},{"time":616809,"text":"a monthly lease payment, which is less than the utility bill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620519,"text":"CA: But you yourself get a long-term commercial benefit from that power."},{"time":624032,"text":"You're kind of building a new type of distributed utility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627796,"text":"EM: Exactly. What it amounts to"},{"time":629471,"text":"is a giant distributed utility."},{"time":632812,"text":"I think it's a good thing, because utilities"},{"time":635695,"text":"have been this monopoly, and people haven't had any choice."},{"time":638532,"text":"So effectively it's the first time"},{"time":640627,"text":"there's been competition for this monopoly,"},{"time":643892,"text":"because the utilities have been the only ones"},{"time":646892,"text":"that owned those power distribution lines, but now it's on your roof."},{"time":649539,"text":"So I think it's actually very empowering"},{"time":651430,"text":"for homeowners and businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654067,"text":"CA: And you really picture a future"},{"time":655425,"text":"where a majority of power in America,"},{"time":659344,"text":"within a decade or two, or within your lifetime, it goes solar?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664046,"text":"EM: I'm extremely confident that solar will be at least a plurality of power,"},{"time":669844,"text":"and most likely a majority,"},{"time":671956,"text":"and I predict it will be a plurality in less than 20 years."},{"time":677216,"text":"I made that bet with someone —CA: Definition of plurality is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":680684,"text":"EM: More from solar than any other source."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682430,"text":"CA: Ah. Who did you make the bet with?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686188,"text":"EM: With a friend who will remain nameless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689588,"text":"CA: Just between us. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":693908,"text":"EM: I made that bet, I think, two or three years ago,"},{"time":696700,"text":"so in roughly 18 years,"},{"time":698503,"text":"I think we'll see more power from solar than any other source."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702060,"text":"CA: All right, so let's go back to another bet that you made"},{"time":703829,"text":"with yourself, I guess, a kind of crazy bet."},{"time":706045,"text":"You'd made some money from the sale of PayPal."},{"time":710822,"text":"You decided to build a space company."},{"time":713258,"text":"Why on Earth would someone do that?"},{"time":715331,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":717511,"text":"EM: I got that question a lot, that's true."},{"time":720324,"text":"People would say, \"Did you hear the joke about the guy"},{"time":722583,"text":"who made a small fortune in the space industry?\""},{"time":725484,"text":"Obviously, \"He started with a large one,\" is the punchline."},{"time":729732,"text":"And so I tell people, well, I was trying to figure out"},{"time":732278,"text":"the fastest way to turn a large fortune into a small one."},{"time":734565,"text":"And they'd look at me, like, \"Is he serious?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":737606,"text":"CA: And strangely, you were. So what happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":742668,"text":"EM: It was a close call. Things almost didn't work out."},{"time":745850,"text":"We came very close to failure,"},{"time":747600,"text":"but we managed to get through that point in 2008."},{"time":750734,"text":"The goal of SpaceX is to try to advance rocket technology,"},{"time":756884,"text":"and in particular to try to crack a problem"},{"time":758838,"text":"that I think is vital"},{"time":760422,"text":"for humanity to become a space-faring civilization,"},{"time":762449,"text":"which is to have a rapidly and fully reusable rocket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767333,"text":"CA: Would humanity become a space-faring civilization?"},{"time":770424,"text":"So that was a dream of yours, in a way, from a young age?"},{"time":774438,"text":"You've dreamed of Mars and beyond?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":777817,"text":"EM: I did build rockets when I was a kid,"},{"time":779953,"text":"but I didn't think I'd be involved in this."},{"time":781349,"text":"It was really more from the standpoint of"},{"time":783334,"text":"what are the things that need to happen in order for"},{"time":787204,"text":"the future to be an exciting and inspiring one?"},{"time":790024,"text":"And I really think there's a fundamental difference,"},{"time":794113,"text":"if you sort of look into the future,"},{"time":795509,"text":"between a humanity that is a space-faring civilization,"},{"time":798966,"text":"that's out there exploring the stars, on multiple planets,"},{"time":802081,"text":"and I think that's really exciting,"},{"time":804293,"text":"compared with one where we are forever confined to Earth"},{"time":807464,"text":"until some eventual extinction event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809752,"text":"CA: So you've somehow slashed the cost of building"},{"time":811504,"text":"a rocket by 75 percent, depending on how you calculate it."},{"time":814848,"text":"How on Earth have you done that?"},{"time":817127,"text":"NASA has been doing this for years. How have you done this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820238,"text":"EM: Well, we've made significant advances"},{"time":822639,"text":"in the technology of the airframe, the engines,"},{"time":825402,"text":"the electronics and the launch operation."},{"time":828623,"text":"There's a long list of innovations"},{"time":831344,"text":"that we've come up with there"},{"time":833512,"text":"that are a little difficult to communicate in this talk, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":839187,"text":"CA: Not least because you could still get copied, right?"},{"time":842600,"text":"You haven't patented this stuff. It's really interesting to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845215,"text":"EM: No, we don't patent.CA: You didn't patent because you think it's"},{"time":847455,"text":"more dangerous to patent than not to patent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850203,"text":"EM: Since our primary competitors are national governments,"},{"time":852899,"text":"the enforceability of patents is questionable.(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":857368,"text":"CA: That's really, really interesting."},{"time":860787,"text":"But the big innovation is still ahead,"},{"time":863416,"text":"and you're working on it now. Tell us about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866155,"text":"EM: Right, so the big innovation—"}]},{"cues":[{"time":867844,"text":"CA: In fact, let's roll that video and you can talk us through it, what's happening here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872081,"text":"EM: Absolutely. So the thing about rockets is that"},{"time":876155,"text":"they're all expendable."},{"time":877697,"text":"All rockets that fly today are fully expendable."},{"time":879959,"text":"The space shuttle was an attempt at a reusable rocket,"},{"time":882093,"text":"but even the main tank of the space shuttle was thrown away every time,"},{"time":885019,"text":"and the parts that were reusable"},{"time":887115,"text":"took a 10,000-person group nine months to refurbish for flight."},{"time":892171,"text":"So the space shuttle ended up costing a billion dollars per flight."},{"time":895757,"text":"Obviously that doesn't work very well for —"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897939,"text":"CA: What just happened there? We just saw something land?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":901159,"text":"EM: That's right. So it's important that the rocket stages"},{"time":905490,"text":"be able to come back, to be able to return to the launch site"},{"time":908855,"text":"and be ready to launch again within a matter of hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911872,"text":"CA: Wow. Reusable rockets.EM: Yes. (Applause)"},{"time":916555,"text":"And so what a lot of people don't realize is,"},{"time":919763,"text":"the cost of the fuel, of the propellant, is very small."},{"time":922361,"text":"It's much like on a jet."},{"time":924065,"text":"So the cost of the propellant is about .3 percent"},{"time":927581,"text":"of the cost of the rocket."},{"time":929483,"text":"So it's possible to achieve, let's say,"},{"time":931635,"text":"roughly 100-fold improvement in the cost of spaceflight"},{"time":934475,"text":"if you can effectively reuse the rocket."},{"time":937555,"text":"That's why it's so important."},{"time":938995,"text":"Every mode of transport that we use,"},{"time":941217,"text":"whether it's planes, trains, automobiles, bikes, horses,"},{"time":944147,"text":"is reusable, but not rockets."},{"time":946483,"text":"So we must solve this problem in order to become a space-faring civilization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949771,"text":"CA: You asked me the question earlier"},{"time":951238,"text":"of how popular traveling on cruises would be"},{"time":955033,"text":"if you had to burn your ships afterward.EM: Certain cruises are apparently highly problematic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":961168,"text":"CA: Definitely more expensive."},{"time":963363,"text":"So that's potentially absolutely disruptive technology,"},{"time":967334,"text":"and, I guess, paves the way for your dream to actually take,"},{"time":971507,"text":"at some point, to take humanity to Mars at scale."},{"time":975304,"text":"You'd like to see a colony on Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977601,"text":"EM: Yeah, exactly. SpaceX, or some combination"},{"time":981138,"text":"of companies and governments, needs to make progress"},{"time":984171,"text":"in the direction of making life multi-planetary,"},{"time":987130,"text":"of establishing a base on another planet,"},{"time":990762,"text":"on Mars -- being the only realistic option --"},{"time":993107,"text":"and then building that base up"},{"time":994489,"text":"until we're a true multi-planet species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997438,"text":"CA: So progress on this \"let's make it reusable,\""},{"time":1000411,"text":"how is that going? That was just a simulation video we saw."},{"time":1004230,"text":"How's it going?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005335,"text":"EM: We're actually, we've been making some good progress recently"},{"time":1008499,"text":"with something we call the Grasshopper Test Project,"},{"time":1011083,"text":"where we're testing the vertical landing portion of the flight,"},{"time":1015259,"text":"the sort of terminal portion which is quite tricky."},{"time":1018008,"text":"And we've had some good tests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021044,"text":"CA: Can we see that?EM: Yeah."},{"time":1023105,"text":"So that's just to give a sense of scale."},{"time":1024748,"text":"We dressed a cowboy as Johnny Cash"},{"time":1026188,"text":"and bolted the mannequin to the rocket. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030043,"text":"CA: All right, let's see that video then,"},{"time":1031995,"text":"because this is actually amazing when you think about it."},{"time":1034026,"text":"You've never seen this before. A rocket blasting off and then --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039733,"text":"EM: Yeah, so that rocket is about the size"},{"time":1041651,"text":"of a 12-story building."},{"time":1044277,"text":"(Rocket launch)"},{"time":1055098,"text":"So now it's hovering at about 40 meters,"},{"time":1059071,"text":"and it's constantly adjusting"},{"time":1060947,"text":"the angle, the pitch \nand yaw of the main engine,"},{"time":1063908,"text":"and maintaining roll \nwith cold gas thrusters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074046,"text":"CA: How cool is that? (Applause)"},{"time":1080359,"text":"Elon, how have you done this?"},{"time":1085033,"text":"These projects are so -- Paypal, SolarCity,"},{"time":1090347,"text":"Tesla, SpaceX, they're so spectacularly different,"},{"time":1093025,"text":"they're such ambitious projects at scale."},{"time":1095610,"text":"How on Earth has one person"},{"time":1098074,"text":"been able to innovate in this way?"},{"time":1100549,"text":"What is it about you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102386,"text":"EM: I don't know, actually."},{"time":1107782,"text":"I don't have a good answer for you."},{"time":1110022,"text":"I work a lot. I mean, a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113657,"text":"CA: Well, I have a theory.EM: Okay. All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115970,"text":"CA: My theory is that you"},{"time":1119534,"text":"have an ability to think at a system level of design"},{"time":1123690,"text":"that pulls together design, technology and business,"},{"time":1127333,"text":"so if TED was TBD, design, technology and business,"},{"time":1130809,"text":"into one package,"},{"time":1133306,"text":"synthesize it in a way that very few people can and --"},{"time":1135665,"text":"and this is the critical thing -- feel so damn confident"},{"time":1139759,"text":"in that clicked-together package that you take crazy risks."},{"time":1144375,"text":"You bet your fortune on it, and you seem to have done that multiple times."},{"time":1149254,"text":"I mean, almost no one can do that."},{"time":1151351,"text":"Is that -- could we have some of that secret sauce?"},{"time":1154623,"text":"Can we put it into our education system? Can someone learn from you?"},{"time":1158047,"text":"It is truly amazing what you've done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1159786,"text":"EM: Well, thanks. Thank you."},{"time":1161795,"text":"Well, I do think there's a good framework for thinking."},{"time":1166605,"text":"It is physics. You know, the sort of first principles reasoning."},{"time":1169229,"text":"Generally I think there are -- what I mean by that is,"},{"time":1173983,"text":"boil things down to their fundamental truths"},{"time":1177358,"text":"and reason up from there,"},{"time":1178749,"text":"as opposed to reasoning by analogy."},{"time":1181335,"text":"Through most of our life, we get through life"},{"time":1183549,"text":"by reasoning by analogy,"},{"time":1184637,"text":"which essentially means copying what other people do with slight variations."},{"time":1188175,"text":"And you have to do that."},{"time":1189655,"text":"Otherwise, mentally, you wouldn't be able to get through the day."},{"time":1194229,"text":"But when you want to do something new,"},{"time":1196373,"text":"you have to apply the physics approach."},{"time":1200105,"text":"Physics is really figuring out how to discover"},{"time":1202353,"text":"new things that are counterintuitive, like quantum mechanics."},{"time":1204998,"text":"It's really counterintuitive."},{"time":1206901,"text":"So I think that's an important thing to do,"},{"time":1209422,"text":"and then also to really pay attention to negative feedback,"},{"time":1213980,"text":"and solicit it, particularly from friends."},{"time":1216101,"text":"This may sound like simple advice,"},{"time":1219567,"text":"but hardly anyone does that,"},{"time":1221989,"text":"and it's incredibly helpful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1224341,"text":"CA: Boys and girls watching, study physics."},{"time":1227703,"text":"Learn from this man."},{"time":1228987,"text":"Elon Musk, I wish we had all day, but thank you so much for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1232477,"text":"EM: Thank you. CA: That was awesome. That was really, really cool."},{"time":1235887,"text":"Look at that. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1238148,"text":"Just take a bow. That was fantastic."},{"time":1242975,"text":"Thank you so much."}]}]}